SIMPLE: submultiple
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Submultiple
<hw>Sub*mul"ti*ple</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Math.)</fld>
<def>A number or quality which is contained in another an exact number
of times, or is an aliquot part of it; thus, 7 is the
<xex>submultiple</xex> of 56, being contained in it eight
times.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Submultiple</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Submultiple
<hw>Sub*mul"ti*ple</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>Of or
pertaining to a submultiple; being a submultiple; <as>as, a
<ex>submultiple</ex> number; <ex>submultiple</ex> ratio</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Submuscular</ent>⟦br⟧
